pullRequest.title: Model part names
pullRequest.bodyText:
Filled in all of the part names based on what Mojang gaves us in their json models work.
Unswapped the spikeExtension and tailAngle field and methods in GuardianEntity.
Unswapped the left and right legs in IllagerEntityModel
Provided names for some of the missing pieces in MathHelper (Thanks to some help from @UpcraftLP )

Notable changes to existing names:
helmet -> hat
cape -> cloak
torso -> body
plate -> basePlate (Armour stands) (Mojang's pick)
hip -> shoulderStick (Armour stands) (Mojang's pick)
*ModelPart named root when used as the parameter to a model's constructor, as it serves as the root node to the model's hierarchy of elements. As such, any places where that part is saved in a model's field is named similarly.
BipedEntityModel.ArmPose.method_30156 -> isTwoHanded (true for BOW_AND_ARROW and all crossbow poses)

commit.message: Update all the models fields that come from Mojang's json code
Fill in missing names in MathHelper
